I"à<p>Welcome to Asymptotic Analysis I! This fits into the world of PDE somewhere between real analysis and analytic methods. On the other side of analytic methods is numerical methods.</p>

<p><a class="page-link" href="/asympI/introduction"> Introduction - What is Asymptotic Analysis? </a></p>

<p>The prerequisites are as follows</p>
<ol>
  <li>A strong background in solution methods of ODE and PDE</li>
  <li>A working knowledge of complex analysis</li>
  <li>An exposure to physics is useful; many examples will be drawn from physics.</li>
</ol>

